What Should Feel True at the End
Looking back from the final session, the party should be able to trace every thread to its independent origin. Calixto was always doing his own thing. The nightmares in Dawnstar were always Vaermina. The vampires were always the vampires. The Forsworn were always the Forsworn. The Guild was always the Guild.
None of it was placed to confuse them. The confusion was a side effect of carrying the real problem through a world that had its own problems and didn't know they were the through-line.
The frozen people on the roads were always Ismara. That was always the one thing they couldn't fix by investigating the local crisis.
They were very busy. She was very patient. That is the whole story.

